# Notes / Commands for correct Git usage

## Branches
- main = stable shared version
- feature branches = active work

### How to create a new Branch: ( Run these in the order from top -> bottom):
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout -b feature/my-feature-name


## Daily working routine:

Before you start coding:
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout -b feature/my-feature-name

While working:
git status
git add .
git commit -m "add post validation"

When working:
git push -u origin feature/my-feature-name

Then on GitHub: Open Pull Request → friend reviews → merge into main
